moor.translation[0].definitions[0].defin: a wild open area of high land, covered with rough grass or low bushes and heather, that is not farmed because the soil is not good enough
moor.translation[0].definitions[0].examp: They went grouse shooting up on the moors.
moor.translation[1].definitions[0].defin: to fasten a ship or boat to the land or to the bottom of the sea using ropes or an anchor
moor.translation[1].definitions[0].examp: Two or three fishing boats were moored alongside the pier.
moor.translation[2].definitions[0].defin: one of the Muslim people from North Africa who entered Spain in the 8th century and ruled the southern part of the country until 1492
